<i>["DREAMER"</I> PLAYS]</i>

22:45.443 --> 22:47.579
<i>♪ Dreamer ♪</i>

22:49.280 --> 22:52.274
<i>♪ I've been called ♪</i>

22:53.384 --> 22:55.815
<i>♪ A dreamer ♪</i>

22:57.910 --> 23:00.480
<i>♪ With no future at all ♪</i>

23:02.926 --> 23:06.079
<i>♪ They call me dreamer boy ♪</i>

23:06.496 --> 23:09.025
<i>♪ Oh, but that's all right ♪</i>

23:09.233 --> 23:11.758
- [CLEARS THROAT] <i>
- ♪ 'Cause I know ♪</i>

23:12.070 --> 23:13.796
<i>♪ I know ♪</i>

23:14.004 --> 23:16.241
<i>♪ That you know ♪</i>

23:16.273 --> 23:18.358
- Hap.
- Florida.

23:18.384 --> 23:20.078
<i>- ♪ I'm more than a dreamer ♪</i>
- Hi.

23:20.110 --> 23:22.235
- Hello.
- Ladies.

23:22.646 --> 23:25.149
<i>- ♪ And with you, darlin' ♪</i>
- You're lookin' good.

23:25.183 --> 23:26.550
<i>♪ I can make it ♪</i>

23:26.583 --> 23:30.149
- But then, you always do.<i>
- ♪ By and by ♪</i>

23:30.922 --> 23:32.089
Well, you look the same.

23:32.123 --> 23:33.568
Hm. Hm.

23:34.224 --> 23:35.626
♪♪

23:37.395 --> 23:38.896
Uh, you, uh...

23:38.929 --> 23:40.397
<i>♪ Loser ♪</i>

23:40.431 --> 23:42.300
You wanna dance?

23:42.332 --> 23:44.002
<i>♪ They say I won't succeed ♪</i>

23:44.034 --> 23:45.402
Uh...

23:45.435 --> 23:47.172
♪♪

23:47.204 --> 23:49.073
<i>- ♪ Refuser ♪</i>
- Sure.

23:49.107 --> 23:50.642
Watch my bag.

23:50.675 --> 23:53.278
<i>♪ To conformity ♪</i>

23:55.079 --> 23:58.095
<i>♪ But I believe a man ♪</i>

23:58.649 --> 24:02.649
<i>♪ Should reach over yonder
to touch a star ♪</i>

24:03.253 --> 24:05.890
<i>♪ 'Cause with his hands
in the dirt ♪</i>

24:05.924 --> 24:08.225
<i>♪ Doin' that eight-hour work ♪</i>

24:08.259 --> 24:11.363
<i>♪ A man just can't go far ♪</i>

24:11.396 --> 24:15.086
<i>♪ You got to be a dreamer ♪</i>

24:15.666 --> 24:17.827
<i>♪ And with you, darlin' ♪</i>

24:18.002 --> 24:19.960
<i>♪ I can make it ♪</i>

24:20.237 --> 24:23.238
<i>♪ By and by ♪</i>

24:24.342 --> 24:26.606
♪♪

24:26.867 --> 24:29.625
<i>♪ I'll dream us up ♪</i>

24:30.548 --> 24:33.251
<i>♪ A paradise ♪</i>

24:35.118 --> 24:38.445
<i>♪ Just you and me ♪</i>

24:39.123 --> 24:42.594
<i>♪ And sugar and spice ♪</i>

24:43.593 --> 24:47.368
<i>♪ Yes, I'm a dreamer ♪</i>

24:49.087 --> 24:52.523
<i>♪ And I'll make it
in this old world ♪</i>

24:54.237 --> 24:56.162
<i>♪ Dream... ♪</i>
[DOORBELL RINGS]

24:57.608 --> 24:58.643
[INSECTS CHIRPING]

24:58.675 --> 25:01.079
[DOOR CREAKS]

25:04.733 --> 25:05.930
Florida?

25:10.931 --> 25:12.165
[DOOR CREAKS AND CLOSES]

25:17.183 --> 25:18.395
Florida?

25:52.033 --> 25:53.204
[CHUCKLES]

26:00.167 --> 26:01.936
[SNIFFS]

26:06.778 --> 26:08.969
[SWITCH CLICKS]
You gonna sniff them, too?

26:09.203 --> 26:10.514
Jesus, Hanson!

26:10.723 --> 26:12.123
Damn!

26:12.149 --> 26:14.151
That's creepy.
What the hell you doin' here?

26:14.177 --> 26:15.805
Shit, I'm a cop.

26:16.035 --> 26:17.375
What's your excuse?

26:18.187 --> 26:19.975
I just figured I'd check.

26:20.124 --> 26:21.593
See if she got back.

26:21.626 --> 26:23.427
You didn't believe me about her,
did you?

26:23.461 --> 26:24.559
Hmm?

26:25.195 --> 26:27.015
Oh, truth is, uh...

26:28.130 --> 26:30.574
I half expected her to be here.

26:30.772 --> 26:32.073
Hidin' from you.

26:32.843 --> 26:34.745
That girl don't hide from nothin'.

26:34.963 --> 26:36.509
That's what I'm scared of.

26:37.018 --> 26:39.493
Don't know when to quit
pickin' the scabs.

26:40.677 --> 26:42.214
Damn.

26:46.250 --> 26:48.670
What is it about women, Collins?

26:50.187 --> 26:52.970
Take cavemen like us,

26:53.696 --> 26:56.059
twist our peckers up into knots, and...

26:56.620 --> 26:58.404
leave us to untie 'em.

26:58.956 --> 27:00.705
Shit ain't right.

27:00.970 --> 27:02.998
No, that's just the good ones.

27:04.180 --> 27:06.804
Best ones twist 'em up
so damn tight

27:06.838 --> 27:09.704
[CHUCKLES]
you can't untie 'em.

27:10.508 --> 27:12.018
Me and her.

27:12.577 --> 27:14.183
Mm.

27:15.125 --> 27:17.212
It was good for a while there.

27:18.348 --> 27:20.125
Then it went sour.

27:20.518 --> 27:22.444
[SIGHS]

27:23.721 --> 27:25.512
Yeah, I know what you mean, Marvin.

27:25.538 --> 27:26.845
[CHUCKLES]

27:26.871 --> 27:28.346
You don't know shit.

27:29.870 --> 27:31.516
Don't call me "Marvin."

27:32.696 --> 27:34.299
I spent a year and a half

27:34.331 --> 27:36.707
in a lovin' relationship with that girl.

27:37.069 --> 27:38.516
You [CHUCKLES]

27:38.586 --> 27:40.023
spent the night
in a truck.

27:40.860 --> 27:42.214
Was one hell of a night.

27:42.240 --> 27:43.875
I'ma stop you right there

27:44.134 --> 27:46.813
'fore you make me do
somethin' I might regret.

27:47.177 --> 27:50.180
Why don't you just go home, Hanson, huh?

27:50.214 --> 27:52.907
Spend Christmas Eve with your kids.

27:53.150 --> 27:55.189
I'll call you when I find her.

27:56.354 --> 27:58.857
You'll wanna check that
answering machine 'fore you go.

27:58.889 --> 28:00.658
[LIQUID SWISHES]

28:02.292 --> 28:03.360
[BEEP]

28:03.394 --> 28:06.263
BOBBY JOE: <i> Hey, Ms. Grange,
it's Bobby Joe.</i>

28:06.297 --> 28:07.464
<i>I appreciate you meetin' up with us</i>

28:07.498 --> 28:09.134
<i>with the holidays and all.</i>

28:09.166 --> 28:10.268
<i>We'll be around at the, uh...</i>

28:10.301 --> 28:12.770
<i>the radio station around
1:00 p.m. with Mr. Knox</i>

28:12.802 --> 28:14.171
<i>to go over all the paperwork.</i>

28:14.204 --> 28:15.706
<i>And, uh, thanks again, ya hear.</i>

28:15.740 --> 28:16.875
[BEEP]

28:16.907 --> 28:17.675
HANSON: <i> Hey, sweet potato.</i>

28:17.708 --> 28:19.751
<i>It's your sugar bear.
Rawr!</i>

28:20.310 --> 28:21.812
[FAST-FORWARDING]
Skip that one.

28:21.846 --> 28:23.615
[CLICK, BEEP]

28:23.647 --> 28:26.885
SONNY: <i> Ms. Grange,
Sonny Knox, 96.6 Radio.</i>

28:26.917 --> 28:28.285
<i>Tryin' to reach Bobby Joe.</i>

28:28.319 --> 28:29.287
<i>If you hear from him,</i>

28:29.320 --> 28:31.356
<i>please have him call
as soon as possible.</i>

28:31.388 --> 28:32.723
<i>Want to get this deal done.</i>

28:32.749 --> 28:35.108
<i>It's a great opportunity for your client</i>

28:35.134 --> 28:36.261
<i>and for me, as well.</i>

28:36.293 --> 28:39.496
<i>Thank you. Hope to see both
of you soon, counselor.</i>

28:39.530 --> 28:41.566
<i>Merry Christmas, all that jazz.</i>

28:41.598 --> 28:42.634
[CLICK]

28:42.666 --> 28:44.040
Hm.

28:44.909 --> 28:47.376
Any idea who the Bobby Joe guy is?

28:47.704 --> 28:49.368
Number was a pay phone.

28:50.707 --> 28:52.299
And the Knox character?

28:52.409 --> 28:53.956
I left a message.

28:54.212 --> 28:56.736
Maybe he's celebratin' the holidays.

28:57.647 --> 29:00.851
I'll check him out
when I get down there, huh?

29:01.057 --> 29:02.858
- Hap.
- Mm-hmm?

29:11.294 --> 29:13.321
Go get her and bring her back.

29:14.856 --> 29:16.547
I'll do my best.

29:16.884 --> 29:18.739
That I promise you.

29:19.272 --> 29:20.665
I'm gonna hold you to it.

29:21.705 --> 29:22.940
Yeah.

29:22.973 --> 29:24.509
[CLICKS TONGUE]

29:25.743 --> 29:28.266
[BELL TOLLING]

29:28.546 --> 29:30.715
[ROMANTIC MUSIC PLAYS ON TV]

29:34.518 --> 29:35.587
Hey.

29:35.619 --> 29:36.891
[INDISTINCT TALKING ON TV]

29:37.487 --> 29:38.455
Hey.

29:38.485 --> 29:40.225
- BOTH: Hey.

29:40.258 --> 29:41.826
♪♪

29:42.217 --> 29:43.320
[DOOR CLOSES]

29:47.646 --> 29:49.098
Leon and Clinton.

29:49.124 --> 29:50.293
I'll explain later.

29:50.319 --> 29:51.976
They're gonna watch the house
while we're gone.

29:52.002 --> 29:53.404
Ain't that right, boys?

29:53.436 --> 29:54.539
Yeah.

29:54.571 --> 29:56.211
Works out good, too.

29:56.237 --> 29:57.813
Got a ant problem at our place.

29:57.839 --> 29:59.146
We're better off here.

29:59.172 --> 30:00.611
Christmas ants, ya know?

30:00.645 --> 30:03.381
Uh, nope.
Not sure if I do.

30:03.414 --> 30:05.817
You know, those ants that only
come out at Christmastime.

30:05.849 --> 30:07.551
They everywhere this time of year!

30:07.585 --> 30:09.287
Our house is full
of those little dudes.

30:09.320 --> 30:10.754
Goddamn Christmas ants!

30:10.788 --> 30:12.857
- They red or green or...
- Nah.

30:12.889 --> 30:16.211
They just come out at Christmas.
They Christmas ants.

30:16.394 --> 30:18.429
Yeah, there's ants
in my underwear drawer.

30:18.462 --> 30:20.379
That's 'cause your underwear
ain't clean.

30:20.531 --> 30:22.300
Man, what you doin'
in my underwear drawer?

30:22.332 --> 30:23.834
You know they ate my banana?

30:23.915 --> 30:25.937
I left it on the table, and they ate it.

30:26.070 --> 30:28.177
[CRUNCHES]

30:28.836 --> 30:29.906
Right.

30:29.939 --> 30:31.375
Oh.

30:32.766 --> 30:35.187
Uh, Leonard.
We gotta go.

30:35.346 --> 30:37.949
You turkeys help yourself
to whatever's in the fridge.

30:37.982 --> 30:40.417
I counted my cookies, so hands off.

30:40.451 --> 30:42.287
BOTH: Yes!

30:42.320 --> 30:43.621
[DOOR CLOSES]

30:44.621 --> 30:46.757
[DOG BARKS IN DISTANCE]

30:46.791 --> 30:48.425
[FROG CROAKING]

30:48.458 --> 30:51.762
♪♪

