31:22.282 --> 31:24.584
♪♪

31:24.617 --> 31:27.421
<i>♪ I went down
to my prayin' ground ♪</i>

31:27.453 --> 31:30.316
<i>♪ Fell down on my knees ♪</i>

31:30.491 --> 31:32.026
♪♪

31:32.059 --> 31:34.995
<i>♪ I went down
to my prayin' ground ♪</i>

31:35.029 --> 31:38.299
<i>♪ And fell down on my knees ♪</i>

31:38.331 --> 31:39.934
Mm.

31:39.966 --> 31:42.270
- Goddamn fly.
- <i>♪ I ain't cryin' for no religion ♪</i>

31:42.302 --> 31:45.871
<i>♪ Lord, give me back
my good gal, please ♪</i>

31:46.302 --> 31:48.205
<i>♪ Well ♪</i>

31:48.309 --> 31:50.762
<i>♪ Lord ♪</i>

31:50.877 --> 31:53.446
<i>♪ How I love to ride ♪</i>

31:55.624 --> 31:58.160
<i>♪ I said, Lord ♪</i>

31:58.385 --> 32:00.340
_

32:00.887 --> 32:02.456
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

32:05.358 --> 32:06.526
Mornin'.

32:13.966 --> 32:15.043
Howdy.

32:15.069 --> 32:18.045
Aw, that's
a fine-lookin' man.

32:18.071 --> 32:20.031
Ain't he a picture, Pete?

32:20.210 --> 32:22.110
- Th-Thank you, ma'am.
- Yeah.

32:22.343 --> 32:23.708
You got a bathroom I can use?

32:23.734 --> 32:26.488
It's broke.
Go around behind the shack.

32:26.847 --> 32:27.915
Oh.

32:30.483 --> 32:32.686
Whatchu doin' with that cracker?

32:32.720 --> 32:33.953
You in trouble, son?

32:33.986 --> 32:36.690
That is one sorry-lookin'
white boy.

32:36.723 --> 32:38.504
What you and him doin' together?

32:39.620 --> 32:40.879
Just travelin'.

32:41.032 --> 32:42.855
With him?
What for?

32:46.377 --> 32:49.711
To tell you the truth,
he had brain fever as boy.

32:49.737 --> 32:51.072
Ain't too bright.

32:51.571 --> 32:53.973
My mama used to work
for his mama when we was kids.

32:54.007 --> 32:57.038
When she died, we felt sorry
for him and took him in.

32:57.417 --> 32:58.484
Grew up together.

32:58.510 --> 32:59.979
Kinda feel a little sorry for him.

33:00.253 --> 33:01.394
- Mm.
- Mm.

33:01.420 --> 33:03.923
That's a lordly thing
your mama did,

33:04.050 --> 33:06.453
takin' in a dimwitted white boy
like that.

33:06.486 --> 33:07.887
- Mm-hmm.
- Yes, ma'am.

33:07.921 --> 33:10.857
But, you know,
I use him as a chauffeur.

33:10.890 --> 33:13.310
This way I can keep my eye on him.

33:13.559 --> 33:15.387
Keep him outta trouble.

33:16.199 --> 33:18.174
Bathroom's inside.

33:18.335 --> 33:21.017
It ain't really broke.
You need it?

33:21.902 --> 33:23.914
- Nice little place you got here.
- No.

33:24.320 --> 33:26.022
[LAUGHING] Hey.

33:26.173 --> 33:28.376
Them boiled peanuts?
[CHUCKLES]

33:28.408 --> 33:30.506
I-I ain't had boiled peanuts

33:31.480 --> 33:33.159
long as I can remember.

33:33.879 --> 33:35.817
[LID CLATTERS]

33:37.310 --> 33:38.872
They ain't ready yet.

33:39.193 --> 33:40.723
- Come here, you.
- Damn!

33:42.042 --> 33:43.137
Yes, ma'am.

33:48.127 --> 33:50.731
Your mama must've been
a saintly woman.

33:50.763 --> 33:52.293
Praise be to Jesus.

33:52.331 --> 33:53.832
Where you boys headed?

33:53.966 --> 33:56.169
Uh... Grovetown.

33:56.203 --> 33:57.637
- Grovetown?!
- Grovetown?

33:57.663 --> 33:59.103
- With him?!
- With him?!

33:59.572 --> 34:01.674
- Grovetown.
- [LAUGHING]

34:01.707 --> 34:03.710
[LAUGHING]

34:04.771 --> 34:06.840
Whoo-hoo-hoo-hoo!

34:06.866 --> 34:08.688
- What's so funny?
- Nothin' funny about it.

34:08.714 --> 34:10.989
Whoo-hoo!
Nothin' at all!

34:11.083 --> 34:12.920
You gonna have
a good time in Grovetown.

34:12.953 --> 34:14.187
- [COUGHING]
- Oh.

34:14.221 --> 34:15.856
They gonna love you there.

34:15.888 --> 34:17.824
[BOTH LAUGHING]

34:19.025 --> 34:20.928
- Y'all have a nice day.
- Ooh, Lord!

34:20.960 --> 34:22.996
[LAUGHING CONTINUES]

34:23.030 --> 34:24.487
Merry Christmas, now.

34:24.514 --> 34:26.206
- Grovetown!
- Whoo!

34:26.232 --> 34:27.777
[BOTH LAUGHING]

34:27.803 --> 34:29.206
Bless 'em.

34:30.770 --> 34:32.940
What'd you tell them
folks back there?

34:32.972 --> 34:34.442
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYS ON RADIO]

34:34.474 --> 34:35.909
Nothin'.

34:35.943 --> 34:37.143
♪♪

34:37.176 --> 34:39.677
They sure were findin'
somethin' funny.

34:40.168 --> 34:41.649
Yeah, well, maybe
they ain't used

34:41.681 --> 34:43.583
to black and white folks mixin'.

34:43.617 --> 34:46.074
♪♪

34:46.321 --> 34:49.574
Maybe when we get there,
you lay low.

34:50.351 --> 34:51.715
Stay in the car.

34:51.824 --> 34:53.503
Let me do the talkin'.

34:53.893 --> 34:55.228
♪♪

34:55.261 --> 34:57.664
Whatchu tryin' to say?
What, I can't play it cool?

34:57.698 --> 35:00.000
Nah. Worries me is you like
confrontation too much.

35:00.033 --> 35:02.903
Well, what worries me is that
you don't like it enough, Hap.

35:02.935 --> 35:04.262
I mean, I been in 'Nam.

35:04.638 --> 35:05.840
I can handle Grovetown.

35:05.872 --> 35:07.073
Not just Grovetown.

35:07.106 --> 35:09.175
It's you in Grovetown.

35:09.209 --> 35:10.944
Well, they don't mess with me,
I won't mess with them.

35:10.977 --> 35:12.579
Well, what about
when they do mess with you?

35:12.613 --> 35:13.681
I bear arms.

35:13.714 --> 35:15.216
Wrong answer.

35:15.249 --> 35:17.818
You know what guns means.
It just mean more guns.

35:18.176 --> 35:21.037
I'd rather be judged by 12
than carried by 6.

35:21.701 --> 35:23.757
I just wanna go down there
and find Florida, not...

35:23.789 --> 35:24.924
Well, me, too.

35:24.957 --> 35:26.260
Not have some kind of shootout

35:26.292 --> 35:27.928
like in the O.K. Corral.

35:27.961 --> 35:29.062
♪♪

35:29.095 --> 35:30.664
Whatchu packin' back there?

35:30.696 --> 35:33.566
A shotgun.
Broke it down, in plastic.

35:33.600 --> 35:34.868
Oh, okay.

35:34.901 --> 35:37.326
Couple of Winchesters,
.30-30s

35:37.703 --> 35:40.191
and a .45 with some ammo
in a lockbox.

35:40.406 --> 35:41.756
You bring the Gyrocopter?

35:42.125 --> 35:43.827
In the lockbox, Hap.

35:43.983 --> 35:45.719
- In the lockbox.
- "In the lockbox."

35:45.745 --> 35:48.249
♪♪

35:48.281 --> 35:49.917
[CROW CAWS]

35:49.950 --> 35:51.986
[MUSIC ON RADIO CONTINUES]

35:52.019 --> 35:53.654
LEONARD: Wait a minute.

35:53.687 --> 35:55.089
P-Pull over right here
for a second.

35:55.122 --> 35:56.257
HAP: Mm-hmm.

35:56.289 --> 35:57.690
[MUSIC STOPS]

35:57.723 --> 35:59.526
This here Devil's Crossing.

35:59.560 --> 36:01.061
[ENGINE SHUTS OFF]
Yep.

36:01.093 --> 36:03.030
Mm-hmm.
That's what it says.

36:03.062 --> 36:04.765
You don't know what this is?

36:04.798 --> 36:06.326
Nope.
[SCOFFS]

36:06.517 --> 36:08.320
But I bet you gonna tell me.

36:08.478 --> 36:10.613
You ain't go no damn taste in music.

36:10.803 --> 36:13.039
Grew up listenin' to that
Pat Boone imitation bullshit,

36:13.073 --> 36:15.174
then you crossed over
to that hippy-drug shit

36:15.207 --> 36:16.910
they was pumpin' in the '70s.

36:16.944 --> 36:19.453
All right, all right.
So, tell me.

36:19.713 --> 36:21.582
What is the Devil's Crossroads?

36:23.350 --> 36:26.319
Well, legend has it,
old blues man came here

36:26.352 --> 36:28.027
and sold his soul to the Devil,

36:28.053 --> 36:29.905
right here in this spot.

36:29.931 --> 36:33.102
They ate each other's turds,
sucked each other's carrots,

36:33.327 --> 36:35.451
some hocus pocus crap like that.

36:36.629 --> 36:38.164
<i>Anyway, that old boy became</i>

36:38.198 --> 36:40.200
<i>the greatest blues man ever lived.</i>

36:42.135 --> 36:44.071
I thought that was Bobby Johnson.

36:44.104 --> 36:45.705
Oh, no!
He just stoled it from him!

36:45.738 --> 36:47.206
Well, who the hell was it, then?

36:47.240 --> 36:49.008
Boy named L.C. Soothe.

36:49.042 --> 36:50.210
Oh.

36:50.243 --> 36:51.779
[SIGHS]

36:51.812 --> 36:54.615
Uncle Chester said
he went to see him as a kid.

36:54.647 --> 36:56.171
Sparks shot off from his fingers.

36:56.197 --> 36:58.051
- HAP: Oh, get outta here.
- Eyes glowed yellow

36:58.084 --> 37:00.007
as he choked on that old guitar.

37:00.187 --> 37:01.562
Well...

37:01.762 --> 37:05.405
I gotta admit, Hap.
I ain't never heard of him.

37:05.635 --> 37:07.391
Yeah, you ain't the only one.

37:08.748 --> 37:12.483
Any blues fan worth his salt
know who L.C. Soothe is, though.

37:15.234 --> 37:18.499
[CROWS CAWING]

37:18.705 --> 37:20.682
- Say, Hap.
- Mm-hmm.

37:20.891 --> 37:22.765
What would you sell your soul for?

37:25.211 --> 37:27.960
If I said world peace,
you'd only call me a hippie.

37:28.827 --> 37:30.433
You <i> are</i> a hippie.

37:30.883 --> 37:32.785
Hippie mixed
with old-ass hippie.

37:32.819 --> 37:34.650
[CHUCKLES]

37:35.166 --> 37:36.523
What about you?

37:36.724 --> 37:38.417
Oh, that's easy.

37:38.732 --> 37:41.093
Endless supply
of Nilla Wafers,

37:41.119 --> 37:42.369
ocean full o' Dr. P.

37:42.395 --> 37:44.131
[LAUGHS]

37:45.698 --> 37:48.749
Oh, we sound like
a couple old farts.

37:50.867 --> 37:52.659
Don't you even think about it.

37:52.939 --> 37:54.107
Your butt feel like yodeling,

37:54.140 --> 37:56.409
you better pull over
and let it out.

37:56.443 --> 37:57.910
Hey.
[TIRES SQUEALING]

37:57.944 --> 37:59.179
What's his game?

37:59.211 --> 38:01.914
The hell?
I don't know.

38:01.948 --> 38:03.417
Damn, he's close.

38:03.450 --> 38:04.759
The hell?

38:05.685 --> 38:08.283
What's he want?
Come on! Pass!

38:08.921 --> 38:11.891
[ENGINE REVS, TIRES SQUEAL]

38:11.924 --> 38:13.660
♪ TENSION BUILDING ♪

38:13.694 --> 38:15.757
HAP: What the hell?

38:15.928 --> 38:18.655
♪♪

38:20.167 --> 38:23.037
[SPITS]

38:23.069 --> 38:24.104
Man!

38:24.136 --> 38:25.759
[LAUGHS]
[ENGINE REVS]

38:27.753 --> 38:30.040
Well, that was neighborly.

38:30.276 --> 38:31.912
[BUTTON CLICKS]

38:31.944 --> 38:34.113
[WIPERS SQUEAK]

38:34.147 --> 38:36.283
Well, maybe we should think
about keeping them guns

38:36.316 --> 38:38.787
up front from now on, huh?

38:39.090 --> 38:43.090
_

38:48.600 --> 38:51.225
♪ GLOOMY MUSIC ♪

38:56.453 --> 38:57.739
[BELL RINGING]

38:57.765 --> 38:59.891
SONNY KNOX OVER THE RADIO:
<i> Merry Christmas, East Texas.</i>

38:59.917 --> 39:02.905
<i>That was a sweet one
from Frog Eyes Johnson,</i>

39:02.931 --> 39:05.834
<i>and you're listenin' to 96.6,</i>

39:06.024 --> 39:09.027
<i>Your Blues Fix,
where the blues never die.</i>

39:09.060 --> 39:11.996
<i>Here's an old classic to put
some bounce in your mistletoe.</i>

39:12.029 --> 39:14.365
♪<i> Ding, ding, dong
what a big parade</i> ♪

39:14.399 --> 39:15.667
♪<i> Ding, ding, dong</i> ♪

39:15.701 --> 39:18.003
- ♪<i> What a big parade</i> ♪
- So much for bad, old Grovetown.

39:18.036 --> 39:19.405
♪<i> Ding, ding, dong
what a big parade</i> ♪

39:19.437 --> 39:22.587
Place look like a goddamn
Hallmark card.

39:22.882 --> 39:25.016
I don't see any black folk, though.

39:25.042 --> 39:26.044
You noticed, huh?

39:26.078 --> 39:27.379
Mm-hmm.

39:27.411 --> 39:30.381
Keep expectin' Rod Serling
to pop out any minute

39:30.415 --> 39:32.317
and give us the damn lowdown.
[CHUCKLES]

39:32.350 --> 39:34.651
You've crossed over to...

39:34.905 --> 39:36.422
"The Twilight Zone."
"The Twilight Zone."

39:36.455 --> 39:38.097
[BOTH LAUGH]

39:38.390 --> 39:40.101
♪♪

39:40.127 --> 39:41.963
[CAR HORN BLARES]

39:42.261 --> 39:43.757
Ho, ho, ho!

39:43.783 --> 39:45.598
<i>♪ The north wind says
it's going to snow ♪</i>

39:45.630 --> 39:47.266
[COIN CLINKS]
Merry Christmas.

39:47.299 --> 39:49.335
<i>♪ The north wind says
it's going to snow ♪</i>

39:49.368 --> 39:51.904
<i>♪ The north wind says
it's going to snow ♪</i>

39:51.937 --> 39:54.351
<i>♪ And paint
the whole world white ♪</i>

39:54.672 --> 39:58.397
♪♪

40:01.212 --> 40:03.648
_

40:07.451 --> 40:09.686
[MUSIC FADES]

40:09.991 --> 40:11.556
Who the hell
are they supposed to be?

40:11.589 --> 40:12.658
- What, them?
- Yeah.

40:12.690 --> 40:14.428
That's the Three Wise Men.

40:14.525 --> 40:16.966
Look more like
the Three Ken Dolls to me.

40:17.261 --> 40:19.530
Three whitest black people
I ever seen.

40:19.563 --> 40:21.033
Hey, now.
Behave, Leonard.

40:21.059 --> 40:22.760
Aw, come on.
They got a blonde wig on Mary.

40:22.786 --> 40:25.994
- I said behave.
- WOMAN: Can I help you?

40:31.346 --> 40:33.498
[BUTTON CLICKS]
I'm afraid we're all booked up.

40:33.914 --> 40:36.621
The holidays.
You know how it is.

40:36.647 --> 40:39.230
I sure do know how it is.

40:39.650 --> 40:41.620
Uh, ma'am, we were wondering

40:41.652 --> 40:44.177
if this, uh... this woman
was stayin' here.

40:44.906 --> 40:46.675
Her name is Florida Grange.

40:49.401 --> 40:51.900
Nobody by that name
is stayin' here.

40:52.230 --> 40:54.233
Nobody by that color either, I bet.

40:54.266 --> 40:55.234
[KICKS LEONARD]
[GRUNTS]

40:55.266 --> 40:56.268
We don't take kindly

40:56.301 --> 40:58.932
to smart mouths around here.

40:59.203 --> 41:01.472
Now, I told you
that lady is not here,

41:01.505 --> 41:04.042
so I'm gonna have to
ask you to leave.

41:04.076 --> 41:05.064
Oh.

41:05.090 --> 41:07.932
I got church service to go to,
and I have to lock up.

41:07.958 --> 41:10.494
Well, we hope you have
a nice day, ma'am, and...

41:10.582 --> 41:13.217
and thank you
so much for your help.

41:14.219 --> 41:16.653
[BELLS JINGLE, DOOR CLOSES]

41:17.089 --> 41:18.489
[BUTTON CLICKS]

41:18.529 --> 41:20.565
Why don't you just
kiss her ass cheeks?

41:20.591 --> 41:22.360
Massage her feet
while you're at it?

41:22.393 --> 41:24.096
Well, I find you get more
with a little sugar

41:24.129 --> 41:25.596
than vinegar, Leonard.

41:25.629 --> 41:27.098
Yeah, well, I was usin' brown sugar.

41:27.132 --> 41:28.334
That always gets me
what I want.

41:28.366 --> 41:30.125
- Ladies.
- Strange.

41:30.305 --> 41:32.073
It's almost as if she didn't like you.

41:32.099 --> 41:33.968
Maybe it was this sexy vest
I was wearin'.

41:34.172 --> 41:35.507
Oh, personally,
I've always found that vest

41:35.540 --> 41:37.656
a little [HUFFS] scary on you.

41:38.197 --> 41:39.794
You check out her hairdo?

41:40.511 --> 41:42.680
Lady gotta have
one heck of a strong neck

41:42.714 --> 41:44.315
to hold that shit up.
[CHUCKLES]

41:44.341 --> 41:45.510
You see the part
where it was braided?

41:45.536 --> 41:48.031
- It looked like a little butthole.
- Oh, gave you a little flutter, huh?

41:48.064 --> 41:49.721
Ha ha, very funny.
[CHUCKLES]

41:49.754 --> 41:50.823
Let's just find Florida,

41:50.855 --> 41:53.058
get out of white-man fantasy
before "Matlock" come on

41:53.091 --> 41:54.058
and you can't find nobody.
[HORN HONKS]

41:54.091 --> 41:55.192
I don't know.

41:55.218 --> 41:57.424
I'm beginning to appreciate
the quaintness of this town.

41:57.549 --> 41:59.131
Why don't you just move here?

41:59.431 --> 42:03.431
♪♪

42:10.341 --> 42:11.988
Or maybe not.

42:12.243 --> 42:15.416
♪ SOMBER MUSIC ♪

42:19.611 --> 42:22.596
Startin' to get that
"Twilight zone" feeling again.

42:22.622 --> 42:24.846
<i>This season on</i>
Hap and Leonard.

42:25.096 --> 42:26.948
We lookin' for Florida Grange.

42:26.974 --> 42:28.791
Nobody knows where she is.

42:28.817 --> 42:30.995
I'm the law and you best
remember that.

42:31.021 --> 42:33.565
Sorry I got you into this mess Leonard.

